        <h1>43,360 students await school closings decision</h1>
        <p>The Chicago Public Schools (CPS) has marked <strong>129 schools</strong> for possible closure based on utilization and performance. However, a school is more than just two numbers and its closing affects long-term student educational outcomes, the stability of a neighborhood, and parental trust in the school system.
The detailed data presented will help parents with children in schools on the closing list learn about current schools and the schools to which they could be sent. </p>
        
